
@*
Procurement Tracking Tool
    CSIS 483 Capstone Project
    Moses Padilla

    Purpose:
    This page provides vendor management functionality for the Procurement tracking Tool. Users can view existing vendors and add new vendors to
    support procurement activities. Vendor information includes the vendor name, primary point of contact (POC), and POC email address.

    Functionality:
    - Displays a list of available vendors.
    - Allows users to add new vendors.
    - Captures vendor name information.
    - Captures vendor point of contact information.
    - Captures vendor email information.
    - Displays vendor records in a tabular format.
    - Provides navigation back to the application home page.

    Notes:
    This page was developed using ASP.NET Core Razor Views, HTML5 form controls, and Bootstrap styling components. Razor model binding is used to display vendor 
    data dynamically and process user-submitted vendor information. 

    References:
    Carey, P. M. (2020). New perspectives on HTML5 and CSS3: Comprehensive (8th ed.). Cengage Learning.

    Microsoft. (n.d.). Razor syntax reference for ASP.NET Core. https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/aspnet/core/mvc/views/razor

    GeeksforGeeks. (n.d.). Types of relationship in DBMS. https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/dbms/types-of-relationship-in-database/
*@



@model List<ProcurementTrackingTool.Models.Vendor>

@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Vendor List";
}

<h2>Vendor List</h2>

<a asp-action="Index" class="btn btn-secondary mb-3">Back Home</a>

<h4>Add New Vendor</h4>

<form asp-action="AddVendor" method="post" class="mb-4">

    <div class="mb-3">
        <label class="form-label">Vendor Name</label>
        <input name="VendorName" class="form-control" required />
    </div>

    <div class="mb-3">
        <label class="form-label">POC Name</label>
        <input name="PocName" class="form-control" required />
    </div>

    <div class="mb-3">
        <label class="form-label">POC Email</label>
        <input name="PocEmail" class="form-control" type="email" required />
    </div>

    <button type="submit" class="btn btn-primary">Add Vendor</button>
</form>

<table class="table table-striped table-bordered">
    <thead>
        <tr>
            <th>ID</th>
            <th>Vendor Name</th>
            <th>POC Name</th>
            <th>POC Email</th>
        </tr>
    </thead>

    <tbody>
        @foreach (var vendor in Model)
        {
            <tr>
                <td>@vendor.Id</td>
                <td>@vendor.VendorName</td>
                <td>@vendor.PocName</td>
                <td>@vendor.PocEmail</td>
            </tr>
        }
    </tbody>
</table>